hink is this? [Aside: #15.] Yes?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "1972.393","u": "It is also a prisoner...a &#39;Mussulman,&#39; who...simply a &#39;Mussulman,&#39; He can&#39;t walk any more to work..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1983.439","u": "What is a &#39;Mussulman&#39;?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "1985.031","u": "A &#39;Mussulman&#39;...who is quite emaciated and he can&#39;t walk, he can&#39;t talk...he is completely emaciated...worked out, used up, who can&#39;t do anything any more. Then he becomes emaciated. Then he is a finished &#39;Mussulman.&#39;[Footnote: His description of a so-called mussulman is perefect. The origin of this nickname is not known. See the book by Odd Nansen: From Day to Day.]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2004.617","u": "What was done with the Mussulmen?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2006.337","u": "The Mussulmen were taken and sent to Birkenau."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2009.989","u": "And there?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2010.400","u": "In Birkenau they were taken into the gas-chambers. Gassed."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2014.444","u": "What is this? [Card number not recorded.]"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2016.406","u": " It could be some youth...it could be some youth from the ghetto or from somewhere...after the liberation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2026.939","u": "And what is this? [Card number not recorded.]"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2030.048","u": " This is work..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2032.161","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2032.614","u": " It is at work [some words not clear]...working in the fields..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2041.003","u": "Oh. Yes. Tell me, what is the most terrible story that you remember from the concentration camp?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2053.558","u": " The most terrible...eh...it was when we came to Birkenau and they took the children with the women and they started to throw them into the fire, this was the most terrible..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2066.101","u": "Did you see it yourself?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2067.077","u": " I saw it with my [own] eyes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2068.853","u": "What do you mean, in the fire? Before the gas?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2070.815","u": " Before the gas. Before everything. They took the dogs and with machine-guns they shot at the children and women...they were taken and thrown into the fire..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2079.960","u": "What kind of a fire did they have?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2081.397","u": " A fire that was a pit and since many couldn&#39;t be burned in the crematories, so a pit was made in Birkenau...a pit was made. On the bottom burned oil and coke and other such that burns, and there they took and threw in the people. They threw themselves in. They already saw it does not make any difference any more...they were thrown in so long...between the wires...pushed in so long...so long until they themselves had to jump into the fire...[long means continuously]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2109.766","u": "What kind of wires?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2111.124","u": " Between the electrical wires [the electrified fence]. The electric wires came right to the...near the pit."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2116.285","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2116.852","u": "They were pushed so long toward the pit...with the dogs and machine guns....for so long till they came so near that they had to jump by themselves into the fire. And then..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2126.971","u": "I don&#39;t understand. Where were the electrified wires?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2128.631","u": "I will show you. Here was the pit, yes?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2131.408","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2131.680","u": "...and here came the electrified wires..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2133.944","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2134.245","u": "...thus. And here the people were driven..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2136.237","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2136.569","u": "Here was the fire. When the people came from this side, they then had no way out. Here they couldn&#39;t. Here were the electrified wires..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2144.084","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2144.808","u": "If they touched the electrified fence they were right away &#39;kaput.&#39; [This adjective normally means the complete breakdown of inanimate objects, predominantly mechanisms such as clocks or machinery.]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2148.299","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2148.369","u": "...went &#39;kaput.&#39; And here they couldn&#39;t but go into the fire. And here they were driven into..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2152.625","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2152.866","u": "...with machine guns, with dogs, with..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2155.140","u": "With blookhounds?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2155.955","u": " Blood-hounds. The big dogs that the SS men had."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2159.939","u": "Hm. Anyone from the family had been there?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2164.013","u": " Everbody was there who...I have no means of knowing...I didn&#39;t see...I only saw people...people are being led...such screams that..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2170.381","u": "And where did the men stand?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2172.675","u": " Everybody fell...everbody went in...and the men worked at it...worked...he was shot...he who didn&#39;t want to enter, he was shot; he also had to be thrown in...at that time was full the whole...the whole court-yard of Birkenau was filled with...with dead."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2191.894","u": "When was that, in what year?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2193.765","u": " That was in the year forty-four."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2195.787","u": "In what month?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2197.387","u": " May...May on the...May, on the eighteenth of May..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2201.824","u": "Approximately."},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2202.760","u": " Approximately. [Long pause.]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2209.883","u": "What do you think should be done with Germany now?"},    {"who": "Samuel Isakovitch", "start": "2213.988","u": " What should be done? I can&#39;t say anything. If there are no bigger heads [smarter people] who should that...who should do something, then I can&#39;t say anything what...they didn&#39;t...they had already visited the camps, they can...nobody can say it...such youth who remained without parents, without...and who have nobody...who can say anything?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2238.708","u": "[In English] Yes. This was the supplement to the same spool of the young Samuel Isakovitch. Spool#7."}        ]
    }
